title: documentation v2
body:
Referencing #26 

What is already done (and we can review it):

- [x]  Simplify URL and folder structure by removing documentation from the path
- [x] Home page index.rst should be what's now Introduction to Rubrix. Ideally, this page will still be the first item of the Getting started block (I've seen this in other docs) but if it's not easy to do, no problem.
- [x] Rename Introduction to Rubrix -> Rubrix docs
- [x] Merge Concepts and Methods into one section called Concepts (I think is a heading issue).
- [x] Complete missing things in Concepts (keep it as simple as possible).

To do:

- [x] Add right-side table of contents (toc) to each page, with a header like "On this page".
- [x] Try to include the video on the home page with autoplay and using either html5 or a sphinx-contrib package (I don't know if the video is already made)
- [x] Complete the home page (what's now Intro to Rubrix)
- [x] Add Community section, with direct links to github and github discussion forum.

title: Add tutorials to docs
body:
This PR adds a tutorials section to the docs. It introduces the `nbsphinx` extension and adds a 'Tutorials' section to the TOC.

It also moves the tests&docs dependencies to the `environment_dev.yml` file. I think i prefer the option to keep all the "development" dependencies there and use `options.extras_require` only for "usage cases" of rubrix.

BTW: We already have the docs public at https://rubrix.readthedocs.io
